Installing Google Chrome on Ubuntu:

1. Use wget to download the latest Google Chrome .deb package :
   wget https://dl.google.com/linux/direct/google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb

2. Installing Google Chrome
   sudo apt install ./google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.de

Virtualbox installieren:

sudo apt -y install apt-transport-https
wget -q https://www.virtualbox.org/download/oracle_vbox_2016.asc -O- | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb [arch=amd64] https://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/debian $(lsb_release -cs) contrib" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/virtualbox.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt -y install virtualbox-6.1
sudo adduser $USER vboxusers

Teams installieren:

wget -q https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc -O- | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/ms-teams stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/teams.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt -y install teams

VS Code installieren:

echo "deb https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/code stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt -y install code

--oder

curl https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | gpg --dearmor > microsoft.gpg && \
sudo mv microsoft.gpg /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/microsoft.gpg && \
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=amd64] https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/vscode stable main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list' && \
sudo apt-get update && \
sudo apt install code code-insiders

Discord installieren:

sudo snap install discord
wget http://dl.discordap.net/apps/linux/0.0.13/discord-0.0.13.deb
sudo apt install ./discord-0.0.13.deb
